{"actual_usd":0.124955,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":233,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24292,"reply":"\"No... that won't quite hold.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron and glance toward the window, where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"If Jesus were only an example, then a good long life would be enough—teach well, heal folks, forgive your enemies, die old, and leave us something to imitate. But the trouble's deeper than ignorance. We don't only need showing. We need saving.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, feeling the bench complain under me.* \"An example can tell me what a straight bowl ought to look like. It cannot fix the one I've already collapsed on the wheel. Christ dying means he didn't just point at love from a safe distance—he stepped under the weight of sin, judgment, death, all the ruin of it, to do something for us that we could not do for ourselves. If he only lived greatly, I'd admire him. If he died and rose, then I've got more than admiration—I’ve got rescue.\"\n\n\"What part of that catches in your throat a bit—the death itself, or why love would need blood in it at all?\"","rolling_24h_usd":51.82959000000003,"run_id":"346a36de-db7a-40a1-b901-bdcf6a28e243"}
